'''Anthony David Junior Elanga''' (born 27 April 2002) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] or [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]].

==Early life==
Elanga was born in the [[Hyllie]] ward of [[Malmö]], Sweden, when his Cameroonian father [[Joseph Elanga]] was playing for [[Malmö FF]]. Besides his native [[Swedish language|Swedish]], Elanga speaks English and French.<ref name="MEN"/><ref name="Fagerlund 2022">{{cite web |last=Fagerlund |first=Frida |title=Så blev Anthony Elanga Sveriges nya stjärna – var nära att lämna Manchester United |website=Aftonbladet |date=25 February 2022 |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/Xq2XGg |language=sv |access-date=6 March 2022}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Manchester United===

====Youth====
After playing for [[IF Elfsborg]] and Malmö FF in Sweden,<ref>{{cite web |title=Elanga efter landslagsdebuten |trans-title=Elanga after the national team debut |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2018/9/p16-anthony-elanga/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209124450/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2018/9/p16-anthony-elanga/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2019-02-09 }}</ref> Elanga's family moved to England and settled in Manchester. Elanga briefly played for local club Hattersley, and was scouted by both [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] before joining United at the age of 12.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Elanga after landslagsdebuten – Svensk fotboll|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2018/9/p16-anthony-elanga/|access-date=24 February 2022|website=svenskfotboll.se|date=5 September 2018 |language=sv|archive-date=9 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209124450/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2018/9/p16-anthony-elanga/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title="Otroligt hög nivå – jag har inga ord för det" |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/mBlBKO/otroligt-hog-niva--jag-har-inga-ord-for-det |trans-title=Incredibly high level – I have no words for it |work=Aftonbladet |language=Swedish |date=16 April 2021 |access-date=17 January 2022 |archive-date=18 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118182720/https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/mBlBKO/otroligt-hog-niva--jag-har-inga-ord-for-det |url-status=live }}</ref> Elanga debuted for the United under-18s at the age of 15 in a 2–1 away defeat to [[Liverpool F.C. Reserves and Academy|Liverpool]] in April 2018.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Lessons learned ahead of Liverpool |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/u18s-prepare-for-liverpool-as-will-vint-leaves-club |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=16 August 2018 |accessdate=24 February 2022 |archive-date=24 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220224153434/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/u18s-prepare-for-liverpool-as-will-vint-leaves-club |url-status=live }}</ref> He signed as an academy scholar at United in July 2018,<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=United's academy intake for 2018/19 |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-under-18-intake-for-2018-19-season |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=6 July 2018 |accessdate=24 February 2022 |archive-date=24 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220224153428/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-under-18-intake-for-2018-19-season |url-status=live }}</ref> and scored four goals in 22 appearances in his first full season playing for the Under-18s.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Elanga learns from tournament experience |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-united-youngster-anthony-elanga-learns-from-u17s-tournament-with-sweden |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=20 June 2019 |accessdate=24 February 2022 |archive-date=24 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220224153431/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-united-youngster-anthony-elanga-learns-from-u17s-tournament-with-sweden |url-status=live }}</ref>

The following season, Elanga played twice for the Under-21s in the [[2019–20 EFL Trophy|EFL Trophy]], both as a substitute. He finished the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom|COVID-shortened]] season as the Under-18s' top scorer in the league with seven goals in nine appearances, and won the Jimmy Murphy Young Player of the Year award.<ref>{{cite news |first=Adam |last=Marshall |title=Elanga wins prestigious Jimmy Murphy award |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/anthony-elanga-wins-jimmy-murphy-youth-team-player-of-the-year |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=17 September 2020 |accessdate=24 February 2022 |archive-date=7 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211207131157/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/anthony-elanga-wins-jimmy-murphy-youth-team-player-of-the-year |url-status=live }}</ref> He played four times for the club's under-21 side in the [[2020–21 EFL Trophy]], scoring twice.

====2020–2022: Debut and breakthrough====
[[File:Anthony Elanga Manchester United (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Elanga with [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in 2022]]
Elanga made his first-team debut for United in a pre-season friendly against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] ahead of the [[2020–21 Premier League]] season; he came on as a substitute for [[Marcus Rashford]] in the 75th minute of a 1–0 defeat. After signing a new long-term contract with the club in March 2021,<ref>{{cite news |title=Elanga signs new United contract |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/anthony-elanga-signs-new-long-term-man-utd-contract-march-2021 |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=16 March 2021 |accessdate=24 February 2022 |archive-date=24 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220224153428/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/anthony-elanga-signs-new-long-term-man-utd-contract-march-2021 |url-status=live }}</ref> he was called up to the first team for the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League]] quarter-final matches against [[Granada CF|Granada]] in April, but was an unused substitute in both legs, as well as in the second leg of the semi-final against [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] on 6 May.

Elanga made his competitive debut for the club on 11 May in a league fixture against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref name="MEN">{{Cite news |first=Liam |last=Wood |title=Who is Anthony Elanga? Manchester United youngster in profile as he makes debut vs Leicester City |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/anthony-elanga-man-united-wiki-20573927 |work=Manchester Evening News |date=11 May 2021 |access-date=11 May 2021 |archive-date=11 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511165139/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/anthony-elanga-man-united-wiki-20573927 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was replaced by [[Marcus Rashford]] in the 66th minute as United lost 2–1.<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Man City Premier League champions as Leicester City beat Manchester United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56990159 |work=BBC Sport |date=11 May 2021 |accessdate=26 May 2021 |archive-date=19 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210519202043/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56990159 |url-status=live }}</ref> He started again away to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] on the final day of the league season, and scored his first United goal after 13 minutes.<ref>{{cite news |first=Gary |last=Rose |title=Wolves 1–2 Manchester United: Nuno Espirito Santo beaten in final game |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57132113 |work=BBC Sport |date=23 May 2021 |access-date=26 May 2021 |archive-date=23 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523210828/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57132113 |url-status=live }}</ref> Elanga scored his second league goal for United on 19 January 2022 in a 3–1 away win against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Brentford v Man Utd, 2021/22|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/66503|access-date=19 January 2022|publisher=Premier League|date=19 January 2022|archive-date=14 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220114020039/https://www.premierleague.com/match/66503|url-status=live}}</ref> his first of the season.<ref>{{cite news |first=Phil |last=McNulty |title=Brentford 1–3 Man Utd: Marcus Rashford gives visitors comfortable win |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59558239 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=19 January 2022 |date=19 January 2022 |archive-date=19 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119224430/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59558239 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 4 February that year, Elanga missed his team's last penalty in a 8–7 shootout against [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] during their [[FA Cup]] tie, knocking United out of the Cup for the season.<ref>{{cite news |first=Simon |last=Stone |title=Man Utd stunned by Middlesbrough after FA Cup shootout defeat |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60266339 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=5 February 2022 |date=4 February 2022 |archive-date=4 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220204233340/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/60266339 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 February, Elanga scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal against [[Atlético Madrid]] in the Round of 16 first leg, the final score was 1–1.<ref name="Bernstein 2022">{{cite web |last=Bernstein |first=Dan |title=Watch: Elanga scores Man Utd equaliser against Atletico Madrid in Champions League last 16 |website=Goal (website) |date=23 February 2022 |url=https://www.goal.com/en-ie/news/watch-elanga-scores-man-utd-equaliser-against-atletico-madrid-in-/blt0718fe1c90c89a25 |access-date=23 February 2022 |archive-date=27 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220427231024/https://www.goal.com/en-ie/news/watch-elanga-scores-man-utd-equaliser-against-atletico-madrid-in-/blt0718fe1c90c89a25 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Nottingham Forest===
On 25 July 2023, it was announced that Elanga had signed a five-year deal with [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] for a reported £15&nbsp;million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=Forest complete signing of Anthony Elanga |url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2023/july/25/forest-complete-signing-of-anthony-elanga/ |publisher=Nottingham Forest F.C. |access-date=25 July 2023 |date=25 July 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Elanga moves to Nottingham Forest |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/anthony-elanga-completes-move-to-nottingham-forest |access-date=25 July 2023 |publisher=Manchester United F.C. |date=25 July 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Anthony Elanga: Nottingham Forest sign Sweden forward from Man Utd |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66301365 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=25 July 2023 |date=25 July 2023}}</ref> He scored his first goal in a 1–0 away win against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on 2 September.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Mauricio Pochettino Suffers First Chelsea Loss As Nottingham Forest Earn Rare Win At Stamford Bridge|url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/video/pochettino-suffers-1st-chelsea-loss-vs-nottingham-forest|date=2 September 2023|access-date=2 September 2023|magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]]|first1=Robert|last1=Summerscales}}</ref> On 26 December 2024, Elanga scored the only goal in a 1–0 victory in a Premier League home game against Tottenham Hotspur. On 1 February 2025, he provided a hat-trick of assists in a 7–0 victory over [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Howarth |first=Matthew |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c62qln7ny5wt |title=Nottingham Forest 7–0 Brighton & Hove Albion |work=BBC Sport |date=1 February 2025 }}</ref> On 1 April, Elanga scored the only and winning goal for Forest against his former club Manchester United.<ref>{{cite web |last=Fisher |first=Ben |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/apr/01/nottingham-forest-manchester-united-premier-league-match-report |title=Electric Elanga haunts Manchester United with Nottingham Forest winner |work=The Guardian |date=1 April 2025 }}</ref> He concluded the [[2024–25 Premier League|2024–25 season]] with a career-high six goals.<ref>{{cite web |last=Furniss |first=Matt |url=https://theanalyst.com/articles/anthony-elanga-stats-newcastle-transfer-upgrade |title=Is Anthony Elanga the Right Man for Newcastle's Mission to Upgrade? |publisher=Opta Analyst |date=10 July 2025 }}</ref>

===Newcastle United===
On 11 July 2025, Elanga joined [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] for a reported £55&nbsp;million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=Anthony Elanga signs for Newcastle United |url=https://www.newcastleunited.com/en/news/anthony-elanga-signs-for-newcastle-united |publisher=Newcastle United F.C. |access-date=11 July 2025 |date=11 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Elanga completes Newcastle move |url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2025/july/11/elanga-completes-newcastle-move/ |access-date=11 July 2025 |publisher=Nottingham Forest F.C. |date=11 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Newcastle confirm £55m signing of Forest winger Elanga |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/ce9x4p492ydo |website=BBC Sport |access-date=11 July 2025 |date=11 July 2025}}</ref> On 16 August, he made his debut for the club in a 0–0 draw against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2025 |title=Aston Villa's Ezri Konsa sees red as Newcastle draw blank without Isak |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/aug/16/aston-villa-newcastle-premier-league-match-report |access-date=23 August 2025 }}</ref> He scored his first goal in a 3–1 away defeat against Manchester City in the [[2025–26 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] semi-final second leg on 4 February 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/401842434 |title=Manchester City 3–1 Newcastle United |publisher=ESPN |date=4 February 2026 }}</ref> A month later, on 18 March, he netted a brace in a 7–2 away defeat against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cm2125r14kpo |title=Barcelona 7-2 Newcastle: What Howe and Elanga said |publisher=BBC Sport |date=18 March 2026 }}</ref> However, despite making 32 Premier League appearances in his debut season, he failed to score a league goal.<ref>{{cite web |last=Maston |first=Tom |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/premier-league-most-disappointing-signing-of-the-season-top-20-2025-26-ranked/blt74e65e761626bf45 |title=Premier League Most Disappointing Signing of the Season: Alexander Isak, Yoane Wissa and GOAL's top 20 for 2025-26 - ranked |publisher=Goal.com |date=22 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Elanga was eligible to play for [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]], [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]], or [[England national football team|England]] at international level.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/OQ4vrV/sa-paverkar-victor-nilsson-lindelof-talangens-landslagsval |title=Så påverkar Victor Nilsson Lindelöf talangens landslagsval |trans-title=This is how Victor Nilsson Lindelöf influences the talent's national team choice |website=Aftonbladet |language=sv |date=5 June 2021 |access-date=20 January 2022 |archive-date=20 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120201740/https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/OQ4vrV/sa-paverkar-victor-nilsson-lindelof-talangens-landslagsval |url-status=live }}</ref> He has represented Sweden at [[Sweden men's national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|under-19]], [[Sweden national under-21 football team|under-21]], and senior levels.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=Anthony Elanga – Spelarstatistik|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/anthony-elanga/a404c4d8-7f12-47a1-b70d-e40d90a43d75/|url-status=live|website=Svensk Fotboll (SvFF)|access-date=20 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118014304/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/anthony-elanga/a404c4d8-7f12-47a1-b70d-e40d90a43d75/ |archive-date=18 January 2021 }}</ref>

Elanga played five times for the Sweden under-17 team and scored two goals, both against [[France national under-17 football team|France]] in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref name=":0"/> He played his first game for the Sweden under-21 team and scored one goal in a friendly against [[Finland national under-21 football team|Finland]] on 3 June 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/9OP9kq|title=United-talangens nya succé – slår till för Sverige|website=Aftonbladet|date=3 June 2021 |access-date=13 June 2022|archive-date=17 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417115735/https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/9OP9kq/elanga-malskytt-i-landslagsdebuten|url-status=live}}</ref>

Elanga chose to represent Sweden at a senior level, citing being born and having spent the majority of his life there, as well as the country meaning a lot to him as the reasons behind his decision.<ref name="Flinck 2022">{{cite web |last=Flinck |first=Johan |title=Fotbolls-VM: Anthony Elanga: "Därför valde jag Sverige" |website=Aftonbladet |date=22 March 2022 |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/Bj1ka0 |language=sv |access-date=6 April 2022 |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417115753/https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/Bj1ka0/fotbolls-vm-anthony-elanga-darfor-valde-jag-sverige |url-status=live }}</ref> He was named in the international squad of [[Janne Andersson]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualifiers]] against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] in March 2022, where he also made his debut as a late-game substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/anthony-elanga-uttagen-i-landslaget-har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-vm-playoffen/|title=Sveriges trupp till VM-playoff – Anthony Elanga uttagen|work=[[Expressen]]|language=sv|date=16 March 2022|accessdate=16 March 2022|archive-date=16 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220316111346/https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/anthony-elanga-uttagen-i-landslaget-har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-vm-playoffen/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/sverige-ar-klart-for-play-off-final-till-vm/|title=Sverige är klart för play-off-final till VM 2022. Vann mot Tjeckien|work=[[Expressen]]|language=sv|date=24 March 2022|accessdate=24 March 2022|archive-date=24 March 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220324221815/https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/sverige-ar-klart-for-play-off-final-till-vm/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Elanga scored his first goal at senior international level on 5 June 2022 in a 1–2 loss against [[Norway national football team|Norway]] in a [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B]] game.<ref name="1-2 förlust mot Norge">{{cite web|title=1–2 förlust mot Norge|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2022/06/1-2-forlust-mot-norge/|access-date=5 June 2022|website=Svensk Fotboll|date=5 June 2022 |language=sv|archive-date=5 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605213023/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2022/06/1-2-forlust-mot-norge/|url-status=live}}</ref>

He scored a goal in Sweden's winning game in the play off finals for the 2026 World Cup against Poland on 31 March 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c8dl97er10lt|title=Sweden 3-2 Poland: Viktor Gyokeres winner fires Graham Potter's side to World Cup|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=31 March 2026}}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Elanga was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

